From d0bbe74bad8d294240e5c5898d0f625f6d131976 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Thara Gopinath <tgopinath@microsoft.com>
Date: Fri, 20 Dec 2024 21:23:33 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 075/124] Merged PR 205: Microsoft:lvbs.conf: Disable config
 options to ensure struct module has same...

Disable CONFIG_DEBUG_INFO_BTF_MODULES and  CONFIG_DYNAMIC_DEBUG_CORE in
vtl0 config so that struct module size is the same between vtl0 and vtl1
kernels. Without this module authentication fails. Another way to fix this
issue is to enable these config options in VTL1. That leads to an increase
in VTL1 size.  For the experimental image it is okay to have these options
disabled. If absolutely needed, after discussion with AzLinux team, we can
reenable these options in both vtl0 and vtl1 config files.

Signed-off-by: Thara Gopinath <tgopinath@microsoft.com>
---
 Microsoft/lvbs.config | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/Microsoft/lvbs.config b/Microsoft/lvbs.config
index b17c7e539b2b..9e606306c0e2 100644
--- a/Microsoft/lvbs.config
+++ b/Microsoft/lvbs.config
@@ -1,4 +1,7 @@
 CONFIG_LOCALVERSION="-lvbs"
 CONFIG_LOCALVERSION_AUTO=n
+CONFIG_DEBUG_INFO_BTF_MODULES=n
+CONFIG_DYNAMIC_DEBUG=n
+CONFIG_DYNAMIC_DEBUG_CORE=n
 CONFIG_HEKI=y
 CONFIG_HYPERV_VSM=y
-- 
2.43.0

